3 D. In cases where the employee of a school district fulfills
4 the terms of their contract and terminates employment for the
5 subsequent year, the employee shall be entitled to the flexible
6 benefit allowance for the remainder of the current benefit term.
7 For purposes of this subsection, "benefit term" shall mean the
8 twelve-month period after the initiation of benefits for the
9 position held by the employee.
10 E. Each school district employee shall make an annual election
11 of major medical health care plan benefits under the cafeteria plan
12 during an enrollment period to be held prior to the beginning of
13 each plan year beginning November 1 and running until December 15.
14 The enrollment period dates will be determined annually and will be
15 announced by the school district, providing the enrollment period
16 shall end no later than thirty (30) days before the beginning of the
17 plan year. Each school district employee shall make an irrevocable
18 advance election for the plan year or the remainder of the plan year
19 pursuant to procedures the school district shall prescribe.
20 Notwithstanding, the enrollment period as set forth in this section
21 shall only apply to an employee’s enrollment in the school
22 district’s major medical health care plan, and shall not preclude
23 the enrollment of employees in additional benefits offered by the
24 district on such dates as determined appropriate by the district.
